Here is a complete HTML file that allows user control of random emoji directions using the specified keys. The initial position of the emoji is in the upper left corner of the screen, and a background image is set. Random emoji monsters and items are scattered across the page.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Emoji Control Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            height: 100vh;
            background-image: url('https://picsum.photos/200/300');
            background-size: cover;
            position: relative;
        }

        #emoji {
            position: absolute;
            font-size: 50px;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
        }

        .item {
            position: absolute;
            font-size: 30px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <div id="emoji">üòÄ</div>

    <script>
        const emoji = document.getElementById('emoji');
        const directions = {
            'y': [-20, -20], // up left
            'u': [-20, 20],  // up right
            'g': [0, -20],   // left
            'h': [0, 0],     // pass
            'j': [0, 20],    // right
            'b': [20, -20],  // down left
            'n': [20, 20]    // down right
        };

        document.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
            const move = directions[event.key];
            if (move) {
                const currentTop = parseInt(window.getComputedStyle(emoji).top);
                const currentLeft = parseInt(window.getComputedStyle(emoji).left);
                emoji.style.top = `${currentTop + move[0]}px`;
                emoji.style.left = `${currentLeft + move[1]}px`;
            }
        });

        function createRandomItems() {
            const items = ['üëæ', 'üéÆ', 'üçé', 'üíé', 'üëª'];
            for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
                const item = document.createElement('div');
                item.className = 'item';
                item.innerText = items[Math.floor(Math.random() * items.length)];
                item.style.top = `${Math.random() * window.innerHeight}px`;
                item.style.left = `${Math.random() * window.innerWidth}px`;
                document.body.appendChild(item);
            }
        }

        createRandomItems();
    </script>

</body>

</html>
```

**Explanation:**

- **HTML Structure**: The HTML contains a `div` for the emoji and a script for functionality.

- **CSS Styles**: 
  - The body has a background image and covers the entire viewport.
  - The emoji is positioned absolutely to allow movement.

- **JavaScript Functionality**:
  - The `directions` object maps keys to movement offsets.
  - An event listener captures key presses and moves the emoji accordingly.
  - The `createRandomItems` function generates random emoji items scattered across the page.

You can copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser to see it in action!
